# Keep the build context to sources + ops scripts. Notably excluded:
# - runtimes/: host-fetched macOS dylibs; the Dockerfile fetches the Linux
#   .so for the image platform itself, and the Directory.Build.props glob
#   would otherwise copy stale mac binaries into the Linux publish.
# - src/Mailvec.Tray/: macOS SwiftUI app, not part of the container.
# - data/, mail/, secrets/, mbsyncrc, .env: deploy-host state that lives in
#   the compose dir (= this repo clone on the VM). The build stage does
#   `COPY . .`, so without these exclusions every on-host build shipped the
#   entire Maildir into the build context and copied the Fastmail password
#   file into build-stage layers. Never let bind-mount state or secrets
#   near the image.
.git
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
build/
coverage/
data/
dist/
mail/
mbsyncrc
runtimes/
secrets/
src/Mailvec.Tray/
.env
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/appsettings.Local.json
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite.bak.*
